> Looking for a taste of everyday luxury? This Ultimate Parmigiano Crumbed Chicken Schnitzel is our best ever version, with premium ingredients for an extra special twist on a classic recipe.

== Mash ==

Bring a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} to the boil.

Peel and chop the @potatoes{450} into 2cm chunks.

When boiling, add the potatoes to the water and cook until you can easily
slip a knife through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan,
off the heat. Mash until smooth with a #potato masher{}.

Stir through the remaining cheese, half the creme fraiche and half the chives.
Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then cover with a #lid{} to keep
warm.

== Mustard Cream Sauce ==

Pop the (now empty) #frying pan{} on medium heat. Add the @wholegrain mustard{17%g},
@chicken stock paste{10%g}, @creme fraiche{75%g} and @water{50%ml}, then bring
to a boil and simmer until thickened slightly, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Once the sauce has thickened, taste and season if needed, then stir through
the remaining chives.

== Tenderstem® ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a medium frying pan on medium-high heat.

Halve any thick broccoli stems lengthways, then stir-fry the
@Tenderstem® broccoli{150} for ~{2-3%minutes}. Add the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated),
cook for ~{1%minute} more, then add a splash of water.

Pop a lid on the pan, or cover in foil, and cook until tender, a further
~{2-3%minutes}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once cooked, transfer the broccoli to a #bowl{} and cover to keep warm.
Wipe out the pan.

== Chicken Schnitzel ==

Peel and grate the garlic (or use a #garlic press{}). Finely chop the
@chives{1}(finely chopped) (use scissors if easier).

Sandwich each chicken fillet between two pieces of #baking paper{} or #cling film{}.
Pop onto a #board{}, then give it a bash with the bottom of a saucepan until
it's 1-2 cm thick.

Crack the @egg{1} into a medium #bowl{} and whisk.

Put the @panko breadcrumbs{25} and half the @Parmigiano Reggiano{20} into
another medium bowl, then season with salt and pepper and mix well.

Dip the @British chicken breasts{2}(pounded flat) into the egg and then the
breadcrumbs, ensuring it's completely coated. Transfer to a clean #plate{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging and discard any excess egg.

Pop a large frying pan on high heat and add enough oil to completely coat
the bottom of the pan.

> You want the oil to be hot so the chicken fries properly - heat for 2-3 mins before you add the chicken.

Once hot, carefully lay the chicken into the pan, reduce the heat to medium-high
and fry until golden and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes} total. Turn every
2-3 mins and adjust the heat as necessary.

Once cooked, transfer the chicken to a clean plate lined with #kitchen paper{}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== To Serve ==

When everything is ready, share the mash and broccoli between your plates.

Slice your ultimate chicken schnitzel widthways and serve alongside with the
mustard cream sauce spooned on top. Enjoy!